{"key":"post-8531972","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8531972</id>\n<content>Make the plenum as large as the filter is thick, or slightly more.&amp;nbsp; Position the fan so the intake faces towards the rear, away from the filter.&amp;nbsp; Hook up that motor on low speed.&amp;nbsp; If it still blows too hard, block off part of the intake with cardboard.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You'll know when the flow is right, because a bic lighter held six inches from the face of the filter will bend 45 to 90 degrees, but not blow out.&amp;nbsp; You can do a poor mans laminar flow test with a bic lighter too.&amp;nbsp; Move it all over the work space, and the flame should remain bent to the same angle, regardless of where you place it.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I'm jealous-that's three times the size flowhood I have.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>8531619</prev>\n<first>8450392</first>\n<last>8531972</last>\n<when>1213678973</when>\n<utime>06/17/08 08:02 AM</utime>\n</post>"}